{{Infobox artwork | image=El Greco 019.jpg | title=Agony in the Garden | artist=El Greco | year=1590 | medium=oil on canvas | height_metric=102 | width_metric=131 | museum=National Gallery | city=London }} '''''Agony in the Garden''''' is a 1590 oil on canvas painting by [[El Greco]] or his studio, dating to his second stay in [[Toledo, Spain|Toledo]] and still showing the major influence of [[Titian]] on his work. It is now in the [[National Gallery, London]].
An angel appears to Christ in the left foreground, holding a chalice in his hand. In the right-hand background Judas and a group of soldiers approach to arrest Christ, marching through a dry landscape without vegetation.
